				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi Johnny,
<br />

<br />
earlier or later, I'll explain <a href="http://bbspam.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">in the blog</a> why the commercial tools are under GPL, why it's ok, and why I do so. The topic is big, but the short summary is: antispam tools isn't something to be developed once and never updated, but they require everyday attention.
<br />

<br />
In particular, I monitor different approaches to stop spam. Your suggestions are implemented by other MODs, and they seem work well. However, I always insist that the forum admin shouldn't make bad for the forum visitors. Therefore, I'd recommend to show the website field on the profile page, after the user has registered.<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
